name: Bulbasaur

attacks.name: Poison powder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: For some time after its birth, it uses the nutrients that are packed into the seed on its back in order to grow.

name: Ivysaur

attacks.name: Spread Pollen
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by any Special Conditions, or if it has any Forte Markers on it, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: The bulb on its back grows as it absorbs nutrients. The bulb gives off a pleasant armoa when it blooms.

abilities.name: Amplifying Pollen
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Poisoned Pokémon with Forte Markers on them instead of 1.

attacks.name: Poisonous Vines
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Shuckle

attacks.name: Berry Picking
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completly still.

name: Phantump
flavorText: This Pokémon came to be when the spirit of a deceased child possessed a tree stump. It now wanders the forest searching for friends.

name: Trevenant

attacks.name: Forest's Miasma
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Forte Marker on your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Jungle Hammer
attacks.text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

flavorText: Trevenant is very kind to pokemon living in the forest. It does't even care if these Pokemon take up residen in the greenery of its head.

name: Cutiefly

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Cutiefly can pick up the auras of living things. It skillfully reads those auras to predict its foes' movements and make fools of them.

abilities.name: Sweet Gather
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for an Energy card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Starflower Blooms
attacks.text: Put a Spectro Forte Marker on each of your Benched Pokémon that have any damage counters on them. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Gossifleur

attacks.name: Twin Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

name: Eldegoss

attacks.name: Drift Away
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Seed Bomb
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

name: Magmar

attacks.name: Flame Spit
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather’s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.

attacks.name: Lava Plume
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Violent Finale
attacks.text: Discard all [R] Energy from this Pokémon, and put a Fusion Forte Marker on each of your opponent’s Evolution Pokémon. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Torchic

attacks.name: Run Around
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It has a flame sac inside its belly that perpetually burns. It feels warm if it is hugged.

name: Combusken

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It boosts its concentration by emitting harsh cries. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

name: Blaziken

abilities.name: Firestarter
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a [R] Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fire Stream
attacks.text: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon. This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. __(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)__

flavorText: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.

name: Litwick

abilities.name: Singe
abilities.text: Fire

attacks.name: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Its flame is unsually out, but it starts shining when Litwick absorbs life-force from people or pokemon.

attacks.name: Eerie Flames
attacks.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Chandelure

abilities.name: Fusion Soul
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, put 2 damage counters on each Pokémon with a Fusion Forte Marker on it __(both yours and your opponents)__.

flavorText: It absorbs spirits, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: Salandit

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Sizzle Swipe
attacks.text: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Salazzle

attacks.name: Ignite
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic [R] Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Disorienting Breath
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent’s Active Pokémon’s attacks. That Pokémon can’t use that attack during your opponent’s next turn.

flavorText: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

name: Jynx

abilities.name: Elemental Shift
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may move a Forte Marker from 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon to another 1 of their Pokémon.

attacks.name: Continuous Slap
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

name: Magikarp

abilities.name: Hidden Underwater
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon from attacks __(both yours and your opponent's)__.

attacks.name: Big Splash
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokemon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

attacks.name: Furious Impact
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 40 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Tyrant's Tantrum Forte
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you amy put a Havoc Forte Marker on both Active Pokemon

name: Piplup

attacks.name: Cold Peck
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Reckless Waddle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.

name: Prinplup

attacks.name: Aqua Shower
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent’s Pokémon. __(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)__

attacks.name: Brine
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. __(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)__

flavorText: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.

name: Empoleon

attacks.name: Recall
attacks.text: Choose an attack from 1 of this Pokémon’s previous Evolutions and use it as this attack.

attacks.name: Ice Wing
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks __(after applying Weakness and Resistance).__

flavorText: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.

name: Cryogonal

abilities.name: Glacio Overclock
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may put a Glacio Forte Marker on 2 of your Pokémon. If you use this Ability, this Pokémon is Knocked Out. You can’t use more than 1 Glacio Overclock  Ability each turn.

attacks.name: Freeze-Dry
attacks.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a [W] Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: When the weather gets hot, these Pokémon turn into water vapor. Cryogonal are almost never seen during summer.

abilities.name: Gulp Up
abilities.text: You must discard 1 of your Benched Arrokuda in order to use this ability. Once during your turn, you may heal 50 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spit Out
attacks.text: You may put any number of Arrokuda from your discard pile onto your Bench. This attack does 30 damage for each Pokemon put onto your Bench in this way.

name: Arrokuda

attacks.name: Flip Turn
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémonwith 1 of your Benched Pokémon

flavorText: After it's eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That's when Cramorant swallows it up.

attacks.name: Anger Strike
attacks.text: If you didn't use Cramarant's Gup Up Ability this turn, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Corkscrew Dive
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémonwith 1 of your Benched Pokémon

attacks.name: Thunder Punch
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Electro Impact
attacks.text: Put an Electro Forte Marker on up to 3 Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's). ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game).__==

name: Mareep

abilities.name: Fluffy
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Static Wool
attacks.text: This attack also does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

name: Flaaffy

attacks.name: Discharge
attacks.text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won't grow.

name: Ampharos

abilities.name: Beacon of Light
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Connecting Bolt
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

name: Gastly

attacks.name: Shadow Drop
attacks.text: Put 1 damage counter on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.

name: Haunter

attacks.name: Mumble
attacks.text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Shadow Bind
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

flavorText: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

name: Gengar

abilities.name: Cursed Call
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on this Pokémon.  If you do, during this turn, attacks used by your [P] Pokémon do 20 more damage to your opponent’s Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance). You can’t use more than 1 Cursed Call Ability during your turn.

attacks.name: Shadow Wave
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t use Shadow Wave.

flavorText: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

name: Drowzee

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that a Drowzee is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.

name: Hypno

attacks.name: Counter Trance
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack __(even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out)__, the Attacking Pokémon is now Alseep.

flavorText: The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum in a Hypno's hand lull the foe into deep hypnosis. While searching for prey, it polishes the pendulum.

name: Inkay

abilities.name: Light Retreat
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any [P] Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

flavorText: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

attacks.name: Heated Hypnosis
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent’s last turn, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Illusion Collapse
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, put a Havoc Forte Marker on 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Indeedee

attacks.name: Graceful Growth
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Healing Hand
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: In search of happy feelings—such as joy and gratitude—Indeedee bustles around, taking diligent care of people and other Pokémon.

name: Gimmighoul

attacks.name: Coin Collector
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic [P] Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes it’s actually a Pokémon.

name: Gholdengo

abilities.name: Will of Fortune
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon, move up to 2 [P] Energy cards from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Make It Rain
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards. If this Pokémon has a Fusion, Electro or Havoc Forte Marker on it, draw 2 more cards.

flavorText: It has a sturdy body made up of stacked coins. Gholdengo overwhelms its enemies by firing coin after coin at them in quick succession.

name: Paldean Wooper

attacks.name: Find a Home
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It's dangerous for Wooper to travel alone. They line up in groups of three or four and help each other as they walk around the wetlands.

name: Paldean Clodsire

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Bog Boggle
attacks.text: If there is no Stadium in play, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It lives at the bottom of ponds and swamps. It will carry Wooper on its back and ferry them across water from one shore to the other.

name: Larvitar

attacks.name: Eat Soil
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent’s deck.

flavorText: It is born deep underground. It can't emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.

name: Pupitar

attacks.name: Devour Soil
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent’s deck.

flavorText: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

name: Tyranitar

abilities.name: Sand Stream
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may discard the top card of your opponent’s deck.

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: This attack also does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon __(both yours and your opponent’s). (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)__

flavorText: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.

attacks.name: Rapid-Fire Combat
attacks.text: Discard up to 4 Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage for each Energy discarded in this way.

attacks.name: To the Horizon
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, this attack does 60 more damage. For each tails, put a Fusion Forte Marker on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Gallade

attacks.name: Powerful Storm
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Oracle Cut
attacks.text: You may turn as many of your face-down Prize cards face up as you like. If you do, this attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card you turned in this way. (Those Prize cards remain face up for the rest of the game.)

flavorText: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

name: Minior

attacks.name: Shooting Star
attacks.text: This attack can be used even if this Pokémon is on the Bench.

attacks.name: Self-Destruct
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 80 damage to itself.

flavorText: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

name: Falinks

abilities.name: Call for Backup
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon __(even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out)__, you may search your deck for a Pokémon that has “Falinks” in its name and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: All Out Attack
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Falinks in play.

flavorText: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.

attacks.name: Powder Pursuit
attacks.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. Put an Electro Forte Marker on the new Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Pollen Hazard
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Burned, Confused and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Sycamore Slam
attacks.text: ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Trubbish

attacks.name: Poison Gas
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Trashalanche
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Item card in your opponent’s discard pile.

flavorText: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokémon.

name: Garbodor

abilities.name: Virulent Odor
abilities.text: Both Active Pokémon have no Abilities, except for Virulent Odor.

attacks.name: Sludge Bomb
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.

abilities.name: Distortion Gate Forte
abilities.text: For each different kind of Forte Marker, choose a Pokémon in play. Put a Forte Marker of that kind on that Pokémon. (You cannot use more than 1 Forte attack in a game)

attacks.name: Dimensional Hands
attacks.text: Put 10 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon with a Forte Marker on it.

abilities.name: Glacial Gauntlet
abilities.text: This Pokémon can use the attacks of Pokémon on your Bench with Glacio Forte Markers on them. __(You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)__

attacks.name: Tundra Wing
attacks.text: Put a Glacio Forte Marker on 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fortune's Favor
attacks.text: ==Draw a card for each Glacio Forte Marker in play __(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Ferroseed

attacks.name: Thorny Body
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

flavorText: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: Ferrothorn

attacks.name: Thorny Body
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon equal to the damage done to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spike Cannon
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

name: Genesect

attacks.name: Destructor Cannon
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Special Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

name: Ralts
flavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.

name: Kirlia

attacks.name: Fairy Steps
attacks.text: Draw a card for each [Y] Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

abilities.name: Spectro Dance
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may put a Spectro Forte Marker on 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Star Arrow
attacks.text: ==This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon for each [Y] Energy attached to all of your Pokémon. __(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) (You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Mawile

attacks.name: Clamp
attacks.text: Until the end of your next turn, the Defending Pokémon’s Retreat Cost is [C] more.

attacks.name: Gnarly Bite
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each [C] in your opponent’s Active Pokémon’s Retreat Cost.

flavorText: Its giant jaws are actually steel horns that transformed. It fools foes into complacency with its adorable gestures, then chomps them with its huge jaws.

name: Flabébé

attacks.name: Flower Gift
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic [Y] Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: This Flabébé rides a red flower. Immediately after birth, this Pokémon begins flying around in search of a flower it likes.

name: Floette

abilities.name: Botanical Bond
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: This Pokémon uses red wavelengths of light to pour its own energy into flowers and draw forth their latent potential.

name: Klefki

abilities.name: Tool for the Job
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for a Pokémon Tool card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Key Slam
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from this Pokémon. If you can’t discard any, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

name: Mimikyu

attacks.name: Imitate
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand. You may use the effect of a Supporter card you find there as the effect of this attack.

attacks.name: Astonish
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: A lonely Pokémon, it conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and other Pokémon.

name: Noibat

attacks.name: Hyper Wind
attacks.text: If there is an Aero Forte Marker on this Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: After nightfall, they emerge from the caves they nest in during the day. Using their ultrasonic waves, they go on the hunt for ripened fruit.

name: Noivern

abilities.name: Windstorm
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench and has an Aero Forte Marker on it, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Echo Burst
attacks.text: You may discard up to 2 Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 60 more damage for each Energy you discarded in this way.

flavorText: Flying through the darkness, it weakens enemies with ultrasonic waves that could crush stone. Its fangs finish the fight.

name: Pidgey

attacks.name: Chirp for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: Pidgeotto

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. Shuffle that Pokémon and all attached cards into their deck.

flavorText: It renders its prey immobile using well-developed claws, then carries the prey more than 60 miles to its nest.

name: Pidgeot

abilities.name: Swift Search
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 7 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck. You can’t use more than 1 Swift Search Ability each turn.

attacks.name: Quick Clutch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.

attacks.name: Mimicry Forte
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon Forte's attacks and use it as this attack. (You can choose Forte Attacks in this way.)(You can't use more than 1 Forte Attack in a game.)

name: Porygon

abilities.name: Conversion
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may look at the top 7 cards of your deck, reveal an Item card you find there, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck. If you do, discard this Pokémon and all cards attached to it.

flavorText: Porygon is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data and entering cyberspace. This Pokémon is copy-protected so it cannot be duplicated by copying.

name: Porygon2

abilities.name: Conversion2
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. If you do, discard this Pokémon and all cards attached to it.

attacks.name: Scan Again
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

flavorText: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.

name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Conversion-Z
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for up to 2 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. If you do, discard this Pokémon and all cards attached to it.

flavorText: A faulty update was added to its programming. Its behavior is noticeably strange, so the experiment may have been a failure.

name: Audino

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

name: Wooloo
flavorText: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

name: Dubwool

attacks.name: Super Charge
attacks.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by any effects on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

name: Squawkabilly

attacks.name: Early Flocking
attacks.text: If you go first, you can use this attack during your first turn. Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Fury Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

flavorText: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

name: Potion
rules: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Resonance Potion
rules: Remove all Forte Markers from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Switch
rules: Switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched
Pokémon.

name: Fishing Rod
rules: Shuffle up to 3 in any combination of Pokémon and
Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your
deck.

name: Jiyan
rules: Draw 3 cards.

name: Professor's Research
rules: Discard your hand and draw 7 cards.

name: Brant
rules: Reveal a Pokémon from your hand and put it into
your deck. If you do, search your deck for a Pokémon,
reveal it, and put into your hand.Then, shuffle your
deck.

name: Youhu
rules: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon, reveal
them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle
your deck.

name: Verina
rules: Heal 120 damage from 1 of your Pokémon. If you do,
discard all Energy from that Pokémon.

name: Hex Maniac
rules: You can use this card only if you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent.
Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.

name: Poké Ball Factory
rules: Once during each player’s turn, that player may search
their deck for an Item card that has “Ball” in its
name, reveal it, and put it into their hand. Then, that
player shuffles their deck.
